# Vision

## Why Playbook Liquidity Exists

Playbook Liquidity exists because discretionary trading has one major weakness:

subjectivity.

A trader can have a strong methodology and still make poor decisions because the process lives mostly in memory, emotion and interpretation.

This project exists to make Gustavo's discretionary liquidity trading process visible, measurable and improvable.

---

## The Main Problem

Gustavo does not need more random strategies.

He needs a system that helps him understand:

- which setups truly work for him;
- which mistakes repeat the most;
- which market conditions damage his execution;
- which rules protect him from unnecessary losses;
- and which decisions are aligned with his real playbook.

---

## Product Vision

Playbook Liquidity will become a personal decision support system for Gustavo's liquidity trading.

It will help him:

- register trades with context;
- score the quality of each decision;
- identify repeated mistakes;
- compare setups over time;
- reduce emotional and impulsive trades;
- and transform subjective experience into structured feedback.

---

## Guiding Principle

The goal is not to remove discretion.

The goal is to make discretion measurable.

---

## First Success Metric

The first version will be successful if it helps Gustavo clearly identify why his bad trades happen and what conditions are present in his best trades.
